An institution with a good reputation
The fixed position in the business provides the company with a strong internal and external image.
“From the beginning, IBM maintained a concept of institution rather than technology enterprise,” says Harvard Business School economist and author of the book on IBM Rosabeth Moss Kanter.
“IBM is not a technology company, but a company that is trying to solve business problems for technology users,” said George Colony of Forrester Research.
As the company itself says, there is a difference between getting into the business and creating a business directly.
IBM – or the “green green” – as it is known in the U.S. familiarly because of its logo, has become in the last hundred years one of the world’s largest companies.
