The airline also has an option to buy 20 more aircraft, which would raise the total selling price to $26 billion, Boeing announced at the Dubai Air Show 2011.
Then, on Monday, Boeing said that Oman Air had ordered six Boeing 787-8s, the so-called Dreamliner, which presupposes fuel savings and spectacular passenger services.
The selling price for six of them is over $1 billion.
