"The quality of these customers in particular is very strong."
Many Middle Eastern airlines are owned by their oil-producing nations.
Therefore, not only do they have the money to pay for the planes, but an increase in fuel prices – usually harmful to airlines, because it is one of the biggest costs – is not so harmful, because the country is making money with rising oil prices.
