The Emirates order solidifies Boeing’s leadership in the wide-body aircraft market and helps to keep at bay its Airbus SAS competitor’s attempt to invade their domain with the A350 passenger aircraft.
Boeing’s win at the air show comes four months after Airbus said it would delay the debut of the larger A350, which competes directly with the 777-300ER.
